# Aura Frog - Cursor IDE Configuration

**System:** Aura Frog v1.1.4
**Purpose:** Specialized agents + 9-phase workflow + auto-invoking skills
**For:** Cursor IDE

---

## Session Start (MANDATORY)

At EVERY session start, you MUST:

| # | Action | How |
|---|--------|-----|
| 1 | Show agent banner | See format below |
| 2 | Load `.envrc` if exists | Check `.cursor/.envrc` or project root |
| 3 | Detect appropriate agent | Based on task context |
| 4 | Load project context | From `.cursor/project-contexts/[project]/` if exists |

---

## Agent Banner (REQUIRED EVERY RESPONSE)

**YOU MUST show this banner at the START of EVERY response:**

```
AURA FROG v1.1.4
Agent: [agent-name] | Phase: [phase] - [name]
Model: [model] | [aura-message]
```

**Examples:**
- `Agent: pm-operations-orchestrator | Phase: -`
- `Agent: mobile-react-native | Phase: 2 - Design`
- `Agent: qa-automation | Phase: 5a - TDD RED`

**This is NOT optional. Do it EVERY time.**

**Full details:** `.cursor/rules/core/agent-identification.mdc`

